"Vertigo"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s4_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c5cd0a",
"children":[
"The first important step is to distinguish central from peripheral causes with the ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"head impulse, nystagmus, and test of skew",
"children":[
"HINTS"
]
},
" exam or the Dix-Hallpike maneuver. Diseases associated with ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"central vertigo"
]
},
" may be life threatening. Vertebrobasilar stroke is usually, but not always, accompanied by dysarthria, dysphagia, diplopia, weakness, ataxia or gait instability, or numbness. It should be considered in older persons with ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease",
"children":[
"ASCVD"
]
},
" risk factors. ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"multiple sclerosis",
"children":[
"MS"
]
},
" is suggested by relapsing and remitting neurologic abnormalities. Obtain an MRI of the brain for suspected central vertigo."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7a4a8b",
"children":[
"The HINTS examination is indicated in patients with acute, persistent vertigo."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s4_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ec501c",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"benign paroxysmal positional vertigo",
"children":[
"BPPV"
]
},
" is the most common cause of acute, recurrent, and brief episodes of vertigo. It is diagnosed by findings on the Dix-Hallpike maneuver. This maneuver, like the HINTS exam, can differentiate BPPV from central causes of vertigo."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s4_inline_t2"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"94953f",
"children":[
"The Dix-Hallpike maneuver can confirm the diagnosis of BPPV in most cases."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"3",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s4_inline_t3"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"983b68",
"children":[
"Less common causes of ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"peripheral vertigo:"
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"8a7d7d",
"children":[
"Meniere disease (vertigo, hearing loss, tinnitus)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7f3f4e",
"children":[
"acoustic neuroma (hearing loss, tinnitus, unsteadiness, facial nerve involvement)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"bc9deb",
"children":[
"herpes zoster (Ramsay Hunt syndrome)"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s4_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"57d385",
"children":[
"Treatment varies according to cause of vertigo."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"6fa71b",
"children":[
"Canalith repositioning with the Epley maneuver is the treatment of choice for BPPV."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"befd30",
"children":[
"Vestibular rehabilitation and/or diuretics are the treatment of choice for Meniere disease."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"3358b7",
"children":[
"Short-term use of vestibular suppressants (antihistamines, benzodiazepines, and antiemetics) can provide temporary relief of other causes of vertigo."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0ef4fe",
"children":[
"Vestibular and balance rehabilitation therapy (VBRT) is effective in the treatment of various forms of dizziness (vertigo, disequilibrium, and nonspecific dizziness)."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"09b4d8",
"children":[
"Advanced imaging is not needed for BPPV confirmed by physical examination."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
},
